A 34-year-old man was killed by a speeding train as he crossed a railway line in Nairobi&#39;s Dagoretti. The victim was crossing as the commuter train was approaching when he was crushed. Police said they were called and informed of the incident after it had happened on Thursday evening. The body was picked up and taken to the mortuary. Meanwhile in Pangani, a man collapsed and died while at an open field. Police said they are yet to know the cause of the death.